<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FCE7FA67A332F9CD" author="Carapezza A." box="[835,1034,1518,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="29 - 40" refId="ref4837" refString="Carapezza A. 1998. New species and new records of Heteroptera from Cyprus (Insecta). Atti dell'Accademia Roveretana degli Agiati 7 (8): 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="1998">Carapezza, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FBBCFA67A27CF9CD" authority="Reuter, 1878" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1878" box="[1048,1348,1517,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Plagiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciloris">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FBBCFA67A39DF9C2" box="[1048,1189,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">P. fusciloris</emphasis>
Reuter, 1878
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FF1AF99BA68FF9EE" authority="Reuter, 1894" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1894" box="[190,439,1553,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Plagiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FF1AF99BA623F9EE" box="[190,283,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">P. albus</emphasis>
Reuter, 1894
</taxonomicName>
form a group of similar species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FC9DF998A4C3F9EE" author="Carapezza A." box="[825,1019,1553,1579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="29 - 40" refId="ref4837" refString="Carapezza A. 1998. New species and new records of Heteroptera from Cyprus (Insecta). Atti dell'Accademia Roveretana degli Agiati 7 (8): 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="1998">Carapezza 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Among them, 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FB10F99BA263F9EE" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1883" box="[1204,1371,1553,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Plagiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FB10F99BA263F9EE" box="[1204,1371,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">P. bipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the bigger ocular index, slightly bigger second antennal segment/width of head ratio in male and the straight process of the left paramere (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FCAEF9DEA48BF9B7" author="Wagner E." box="[778,947,1623,1650]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="1 - 483" refId="ref5995" refString="Wagner E. 1975. Die Miridae Hahn, 1831, des Mitelmeerraumes und der Makaronesischen Inseln (Hemiptera, Heteroptera). Vol 3. Entomologische Abhandlungen 40 (Suppl.): 1 - 483." type="book chapter" year="1975">Wagner, 1975</bibRefCitation>
). It has two subspecies, nominotypical subspecies and 
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FEC8F9F2A53DF951" box="[364,517,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">
P. b. 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FE05F9F3A53DF951" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1901" box="[417,517,1658,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Psallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicans">albicans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FDB0F9F3A482F951" baseAuthorityName="Reuter" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[532,954,1658,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Plagiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipunctatus" subSpecies="albicans">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FDB0F9F3A482F951" box="[532,954,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">Plagiognathus bipunctatus albicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FB12F9F3A24EF951" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1901" box="[1206,1398,1658,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Psallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicans">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FB12F9F3A24EF951" box="[1206,1398,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">Psallus albicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F326766EFFBCFFA2FEA4F914A69AF972" box="[256,418,1693,1719]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FE10F917A576F97D" author="Reuter O. M." box="[436,590,1694,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="161 - 194" refId="ref5603" refString="Reuter O. M. 1901. Capsidae rossicae. Ofversigt af Finska Vetenskapssocietetens Forhandlingar B 43: 161 - 194." type="journal article" year="1901">Reuter 1901</bibRefCitation>
). It is characterized by almost to completely pale yellow vestiture, pale yellow coloration of dorsum and absence of black spot at the base of each tibia. This taxon was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FE04F96CA570F93B" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1883" box="[416,584,1764,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Plagiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FE04F96CA570F93B" box="[416,584,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">P. bipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FDD2F96DA401F93B" author="Kerzhner I. M." box="[630,825,1764,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="634 - 645" refId="ref5191" refString="Kerzhner I. M. 1970. New and little-known capsid bugs (Heteroptera, Miridae) from the USSR and Mongolia. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 49: 634 - 645." type="journal article" year="1970">Kerzhner (1970)</bibRefCitation>
without any comments. Later it was resurrected in the subspecies rank by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFBCFFA2FE56F88EA5F3F8E4" author="Linnavuori R. E." box="[498,715,1799,1825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" pagination="369 - 414" refId="ref5274" refString="Linnavuori R. E. 2010. Studies on the Miridae (Phylinae, addenda to Deraeocorinae and Orthotylinae) of Khuzestan and the adjacent provinces of Iran (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 50 (2): 369 - 414." type="journal article" year="2010">Linnavuori (2010)</bibRefCitation>
based on pale specimens collected from different regions in 
<collectingCountry id="F326766EFFBCFFA2FF79F8A2A628F880" box="[221,272,1835,1861]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The nominotypical subspecies differs from 
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FCBBF8A2A4F8F881" box="[799,960,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">
P. b. 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FCF8F8A3A4F8F881" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1901" box="[860,960,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Psallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicans">albicans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
by the black vestiture, whitish green coloration of body dorsum and the presence of a black spot at the base of at least the hind tibia (or on each tibia in 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FEF5F8F8A6C7F84E" box="[337,511,1905,1931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" rank="variety" variety="picticornis">
var. 
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FE24F8FBA6C7F84E" box="[384,511,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">picticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="130A2A7BFFBCFFA2FDBDF8F8A54FF84E" box="[537,631,1905,1931]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[305,1266,368,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-16@7.[305,1283,362,1892]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Plagiognathus spp. A. P. ozgurkocaki sp. nov., ♂, paratype (LEMT). B. P. marivanensis Linnavuori, 2010, ♂ (BCIT), Karaman. C. P. bipunctatus albicans (Reuter, 1901), ♂ (BCIT), Karaman. D. P. bipunctatus bipunctatus, ♂ (BCIT), İzmir. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6402847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6402847/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). We examined a long series of specimens collected from different localities at different times in Karaman. The specimens perfectly fit the description of 
<emphasis id="B945EAECFFBCFFA2FB76F81CA24EF86B" box="[1234,1398,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="154">
P. b. 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D7DFFBCFFA2FAB6F81DA24EF86B" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1901" box="[1298,1398,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Psallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicans">albicans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
with whitish yellow coloration, partly to totally pale yellow vestiture and lack of black spots at the base of tibial spines and the femoral-tibial junction. These records greatly enlarge the known distribution this subspecies to the West (
<figureCitation id="130A2A7BFFB2FFACFDB2FEA5A559FE82" box="[534,609,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1283,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-192@8.[189,1398,1283,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 5. Distribution of Plagiognathus spp. Star: P. ozgurkocaki sp. nov.; circle: P. marivanensis Linnavuori, 2010; square: P. bipunctatus albicans (Reuter, 1901). Grey color indicates previous literature records, red color indicates new records presented in this paper." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6402849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6402849/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="156">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B0FFFB2FFACFD56FEA5A4F5FE83" author="Linnavuori R. E." box="[754,973,300,326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="156" pagination="369 - 414" refId="ref5274" refString="Linnavuori R. E. 2010. Studies on the Miridae (Phylinae, addenda to Deraeocorinae and Orthotylinae) of Khuzestan and the adjacent provinces of Iran (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 50 (2): 369 - 414." type="journal article" year="2010">Linnavuori (2010)</bibRefCitation>
mentions that he has not observed any intermediate specimens among the ones he examined, some of the specimens from Karaman have predominantly black vestiture which very closely resemble the nominotypical subspecies and differ from it by the lack of black spot at femoral-tibial junction of hind tibiae and presence of scarce pale setae.
</paragraph>
